    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>Numerical differentiation via difference quotients suffers from cancellation error: too-small h makes (f(c+h) - f(c)) lose significant digits. The sweet spot is around h = 10^-8 for double precision. The exact derivative is a limit, not a computation.</p>

